Python Variables
A variable is a location in memory used to store some data (value).

We use the assignment operator (=) to assign values to a variable. Any type of value can be assigned to any valid variable.

a = 8
b = 4.32
c = "Hello"

In Python, multiple assignments can be made in a single statement as follows:

a, b, c = 5, 3.2, "Hello"

Data types in Python - 
Integers, floating point numbers and complex numbers falls under Python numbers category. They are defined as int, float and complex class
in Python.
